dct_title_s: New York entrance : America’s Cup races
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by hachures. Depths shown by soundings. "Published Oct. 1899 ... from data furnished by the United States Coast and Geodetic Survey H.S. Pritchard, Supt." Text on adjoining leaf: Match for the America's Cup commencing October 3rd, Shamrock-Columbia, 1899. Rules for match on verso signed: Regatta Committee. Originally issued as bifolium folded to 22 x 17 cm. Historic Maps copy has contemporary pencil notes.
dct_publisher_sm: [New York] : New York Yacht Club, 1899 (N.Y. : Julius Bien & Co.)
dct_subject_sm: Nautical charts—New York Harbor (N.Y. and N.J.)—1899
dcat_theme_sm: Nautical charts—New York Harbor (N.Y. and N.J.)—1899
